<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — QuiKey AI Hub (macOS)"
  description="How QuiKey AI Hub handles your data: AI providers you choose, local storage, optional analytics, and no QuiKey server storage of your content."
  productName="QuiKey AI Hub"
  navLinks={[
    { href: '/aihub/', label: 'AI Hub' },
    { href: '/aihub/#download', label: 'Download' },
    { href: '/blog', label: 'Blog' },
  ]}
  footerLinks={[
    { href: '/aihub/', label: 'AI Hub' },
    { href: '/aihub/privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
    { href: '/aihub/app-privacy-labels', label: 'App Privacy (labels)' },
    { href: '/aihub/terms', label: 'Terms' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="privacy-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="privacy-content">
        <h1>Privacy Policy — QuiKey AI Hub</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>QuiKey AI Hub</strong> (“AI Hub”, “the App”, “we”, “us”) handles
          information when you use the macOS app. It is written to align with the Mac App Store
          <a href="/aihub/app-privacy-labels">privacy nutrition label</a> and App Store Connect disclosures. Structure
          follows patterns used in our other App Store–reviewed products (clear categories, plain language, and a
          concise data table).
        </p>

        <h2>What AI Hub does</h2>
        <p>
          AI Hub runs on your Mac. It helps you run AI actions on files and selected text (Finder and Services), and use
          AI chats and squads inside the app. This flavor <strong>does not include Gmail or Google Drive upload</strong>
          features—other QuiKey flavors have their own privacy descriptions.
        </p>

        <h2>Information involved</h2>
        <p>The App may involve the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Content you send to AI providers:</strong> files, selected text, prompts, and related context when
            <em>you</em> start an action. That content goes to the third-party provider you configured, not to a QuiKey
            “AI backend.”
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Data stored locally:</strong> settings, API keys or credentials you enter, conversation history, and
            diagnostic logs (on device), as the App needs to function.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Optional analytics:</strong> if you turn on usage metrics, pseudonymous events (for example a device
            identifier and feature usage). Not your file bodies or chat text.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Purchases and licensing:</strong> metadata from Apple and/or commerce providers (for example Lemon
            Squeezy) when you buy or restore a license.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Support:</strong> if you email us, we receive what you send (message content, attachments you
            choose).
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data categories, collection, use, and recipients</h2>
        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table class="privacy-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Data category</th>
                <th>How it arises</th>
                <th>How it is used</th>
                <th>Who may receive it</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Files, selected text, prompts, and request context</td>
                <td>You run a Finder, Services, or in-app AI action</td>
                <td>To perform the AI or automation step you requested</td>
                <td>
                  The third-party AI or tooling provider you configured (for example OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini,
                  OpenRouter). Governed by that provider’s terms and privacy policy.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>App settings, credentials, chat history, local logs</td>
                <td>Stored by the App on your Mac as you use it</td>
                <td>App functionality, session continuity, troubleshooting on your device</td>
                <td>Stays on your Mac unless you use separate backup/sync outside the App</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Pseudonymous usage and diagnostic signals</td>
                <td>Only if you enable “Send usage metrics” in Settings</td>
                <td>Improve stability and understand feature usage</td>
                <td>Our configured analytics provider (see <a href="/aihub/app-privacy-labels">App Privacy labels</a>)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Purchase and entitlement metadata</td>
                <td>When you purchase, restore, or validate a license</td>
                <td>Provide paid features and verify entitlements</td>
                <td>Apple and/or commerce providers (for example Lemon Squeezy) per their flows</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Support messages</td>
                <td>When you contact support</td>
                <td>Respond to your request</td>
                <td>Our support mailbox and processors we use to operate email</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2>Third-party AI and services</h2>
        <p>
          Providers you enable handle content under their own policies. Links for convenience:
          <a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenAI</a>,
          <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Anthropic</a>,
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google</a>,
          <a href="https://openrouter.ai/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenRouter</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Optional analytics</h2>
        <p>
          The App does not require analytics to function. If you enable usage metrics, you can disable them in
          <strong>Settings → General → “Send usage metrics.”</strong> When disabled, the analytics SDK is not initialized
          for that configuration.
        </p>

        <h2>No sale of personal information; advertising</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. The App does not use IDFA-style cross-app advertising trackers.
          Optional product analytics (when enabled) is for operating and improving the App, not for third-party ads.
        </p>

